{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"path":1,"lang":2,"translations":3},"/langs/en/posts/delete-html-tags-py-django/","en",{"lang":2,"author":4,"siteName":5,"siteDescription":6,"categories":7,"Categories":8,"RecentPosts":9,"NoPosts":10,"SubscribeTo":11,"AboutMe":12,"AllPosts":13},"Carlos Martin Sanchez","Carlos Say's Bla Bla","What is going on in my mind and its surroundings","categories","Categories","Recent posts","There are no posts","Subscribe to the feed","About me","All posts"],"uses":{"params":["lang"],"url":1},"slash":"always"},{"type":"data","data":[{"html":1,"props":2,"jsonLd":17},"\u003Cdiv id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n\u003Cdiv id=\"toctitle\">Table of Contents\u003C/div>\n\u003Cul class=\"sectlevel1\">\n\u003Cli>\u003Ca href=\"#_con_python\">Con Python\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Ca href=\"#_django\">Django\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv id=\"preamble\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"sectionbody\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>A continuación veremos cómo eliminar las etiquetas HTML de una cadena de caracteres.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"sect1\">\n\u003Ch2 id=\"_con_python\">Con \u003Ca href=\"https://www.python.org\">Python\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"sectionbody\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>Función encargada de eliminar las etiquetas HTML:\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"listingblock\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"title\">main.py\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"content\">\n\u003Cpre class=\"highlight\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\">\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">import\u003C/span> re\n\n\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">def\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-title function_\">strip_tags\u003C/span>(\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-params\">value\u003C/span>):\n    \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">return\u003C/span> re.sub(\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-string\">r&#x27;&lt;[^&gt;]*?&gt;&#x27;\u003C/span>, \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;&#x27;\u003C/span>, value)\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>Vamos a hacer una prueba un fragmento de HTML a la función \u003Ccode>strip_tags\u003C/code>:\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"listingblock\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"title\">main.py\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"content\">\n\u003Cpre class=\"highlight\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\">\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">import\u003C/span> re\n\n\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">def\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-title function_\">strip_tags\u003C/span>(\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-params\">value\u003C/span>):\n    \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">return\u003C/span> re.sub(\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-string\">r&#x27;&lt;[^&gt;]*?&gt;&#x27;\u003C/span>, \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;&#x27;\u003C/span>, value)\n\nhtml_text = \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;&quot;&quot;\n    &lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;\n    &lt;html&gt;\n        &lt;head&gt;\n            &lt;title&gt;Title&lt;/title&gt;\n        &lt;/head&gt;\n        &lt;body&gt;\n            &lt;p&gt;Paragraph&lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;/body&gt;\n    &lt;/html&gt;&quot;&quot;&quot;\u003C/span>\n\n\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-built_in\">print\u003C/span>(strip_tags(html_text))\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>Si ejecutamos el script tenemos como resultado:\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"listingblock\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"content\">\n\u003Cpre class=\"highlight\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-bash\" data-lang=\"bash\">Title\n\nParagraph\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>Si con \u003Ca href=\"https://www.python.org\">Python\u003C/a> ha sido fácil, vamos a ver con \u003Ca href=\"https://www.djangoproject.com\">Django\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"sect1\">\n\u003Ch2 id=\"_django\">\u003Ca href=\"https://www.djangoproject.com\">Django\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"sectionbody\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.djangoproject.com\">Django\u003C/a> una ofrece función para esto: \u003Ca href=\"https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/ref/utils/#django.utils.html.strip_tags\">strip_tags\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"paragraph\">\n\u003Cp>Antes, solo hay que instalar la librería: \u003Ccode>pip install django\u003C/code>.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"listingblock\">\n\u003Cdiv class=\"title\">main.py\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"content\">\n\u003Cpre class=\"highlight\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\">\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">from\u003C/span> django.utils.html \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-keyword\">import\u003C/span> strip_tags\n\nhtml_text = \u003Cspan class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;&quot;&quot;\n    &lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;\n    &lt;html&gt;\n        &lt;head&gt;\n            &lt;title&gt;Title&lt;/title&gt;\n        &lt;/head&gt;\n        &lt;body&gt;\n            &lt;p&gt;Paragraph&lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;/body&gt;\n    &lt;/html&gt;&quot;&quot;&quot;\u003C/span>\n\n\u003Cspan class=\"hljs-built_in\">print\u003C/span> (strip_tags(html_text))\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>",{"title":3,"lang":4,"summary":5,"slug":6,"keywords":7,"filepath":11,"dirpath":12,"created":13,"modified":13,"otherLangs":14,"author":15,"previewimage":-1,"path":16},"Eliminar etiquetas HTML","en","Cómo eliminar etiquetas HTML utilizando Python o más fácil aún, utilizando Django","delete-html-tags-py-django",[8,9,10],"Python","Django","HTML","/static/posts/delete-html-tags-py-django.es.adoc","/static/posts",1349170200000,[4],"Carlos","/langs/es/posts/delete-html-tags-py-django","\u003Cscript type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"Webpage\",\"@id\":\"https://google.com/article\"},\"headline\":\"Eliminar etiquetas HTML\",\"alternativeHeadline\":\"Cómo eliminar etiquetas HTML utilizando Python o más fácil aún, utilizando Django\",\"description\":\"Cómo eliminar etiquetas HTML utilizando Python o más fácil aún, utilizando Django\",\"datePublished\":\"2012-10-02T09:30:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2012-10-02T09:30:00.000Z\",\"keywords\":[\"Python\",\"Django\",\"HTML\"],\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"Carlos\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"Carlos\"}}\u003C/script>"],"uses":{"params":["slug","lang"]}}]}
